  "school": "Smart Money Concepts (SMC)",
  "definition": "A pullback pattern where price temporarily breaks a key level to sweep liquidity before reversing in the direction of the larger trend, often leading to a strong move.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Price approaches a key level such as a swing low or swing high.",
    "Price temporarily breaks the key level, sweeping liquidity.",
    "Price then reverses and moves strongly in the original trend direction."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Used as a high-probability entry point; traders wait for the sweep and reversal confirmation before entering in the direction of the trend, anticipating a strong continuation.",
